1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,583
[mysterious music playing]

2
00:00:03,666 --> 00:00:05,625
[Ryuzu gasps]

3
00:00:07,666 --> 00:00:09,416
[groans]

4
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,500
[Garfiel shuddering]

5
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:15,458
[Ryuzu panting]

6
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:25,416
[Garfiel moans]

7
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:27,666
- [grunting]
- [pounding]

8
00:00:29,708 --> 00:00:31,541
- Young Gar, stop that!

9
00:00:31,625 --> 00:00:33,333
- [grunting]

10
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:42,041
[grunting and pounding continue]

11
00:00:46,375 --> 00:00:49,083
[sobbing]

12
00:00:52,416 --> 00:00:53,833
- Please, Young Gar.

13
00:00:54,375 --> 00:00:59,083
- [wails]

14
00:01:03,666 --> 00:01:04,958
SUBARU: Otto, you idiot.

15
00:01:05,041 --> 00:01:08,541
Guess you did do
something crazy, didn't you?

16
00:01:08,625 --> 00:01:11,833
- I never realized the little
pipsqueak had it in him.

17
00:01:11,916 --> 00:01:15,375
And on top of everything else,
he even won Ram over.

18
00:01:15,458 --> 00:01:17,458
Now here I am lookin' like this!

19
00:01:17,541 --> 00:01:19,125
- Wait. Ram?

20
00:01:19,208 --> 00:01:20,291
What happened to them?

21
00:01:20,375 --> 00:01:22,208
- Listen, whatever
you guys are plannin'

22
00:01:22,291 --> 00:01:24,333
don't mean a damn thing to me.

23
00:01:24,416 --> 00:01:25,208
- You didn't kill them, did you?

24
00:01:25,291 --> 00:01:27,833
- It don't mean a damn thing!
I told you!

25
00:01:27,916 --> 00:01:29,625
Get out of the way.

26
00:01:29,708 --> 00:01:32,500
I'm gonna smash up the entrance
to this stupid place

27
00:01:32,583 --> 00:01:34,666
and put an end to this bullshit
once and for all.

28
00:01:34,750 --> 00:01:36,375
- You can't be serious.

29
00:01:36,458 --> 00:01:38,541
If you do that, the Sanctuary
will be closed off forever.

30
00:01:38,625 --> 00:01:40,875
Is that what you want?

31
00:01:40,958 --> 00:01:43,416
- Hell yeah, it is.

32
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:46,416
Every other thing around here
is what's causing the problem.

33
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:53,458
[wind blowing]

34
00:01:56,791 --> 00:01:57,708
Huh?

35
00:02:02,291 --> 00:02:05,750
Now just what are you
tryin' to pull, huh?!

36
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:07,375
- I'm curious.

37
00:02:07,458 --> 00:02:08,708
Garfiel, what is it
that you're so afraid of?

38
00:02:08,791 --> 00:02:11,750
- [gasps] What are you sayin'?

39
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:13,458
You think
I'm scared or somethin'?

40
00:02:13,541 --> 00:02:15,541
EMILIA: I know you are.

41
00:02:15,625 --> 00:02:16,833
That's why
you're always shouting

42
00:02:16,916 --> 00:02:19,708
and trying to make yourself
look bigger, isn't it?

43
00:02:19,791 --> 00:02:20,666
- Is that right?

44
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:22,291
Well, I don't wanna hear it!

45
00:02:22,375 --> 00:02:23,500
What do you know
about me anyway?!

46
00:02:23,583 --> 00:02:25,500
- More than you think.

47
00:02:25,583 --> 00:02:28,041
Because I was just like you.

48
00:02:28,125 --> 00:02:29,541
I've been afraid of many things
throughout my life.

49
00:02:29,625 --> 00:02:32,583
I lived in fear...

50
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:34,708
right up until today.

51
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:36,625
I left the bad things
in Puck's hands

52
00:02:36,708 --> 00:02:38,208
so I could forget them,

53
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:39,541
but now
I've finally remembered.

54
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:40,833
- Shut your mouth.

55
00:02:40,916 --> 00:02:43,833
- I'm still not sure
what I need to do,

56
00:02:43,916 --> 00:02:45,541
at least, not yet,

57
00:02:45,625 --> 00:02:49,000
but my goal is to find
out
just what that something
is.

58
00:02:49,083 --> 00:02:49,958
Although...

59
00:02:50,041 --> 00:02:50,958
- Shut the hell up.

60
00:02:51,041 --> 00:02:52,416
You know nothing.

61
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:55,083
Don't you--
Don't you dare pretend to--

62
00:02:55,166 --> 00:02:57,458
- But you might be ahead of me,
since you've already found

63
00:02:57,541 --> 00:02:58,916
that one thing for yourself,
haven't you?

64
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,000
- I said
keep your damn mouth shut!

65
00:03:00,083 --> 00:03:04,208
- You're just
way too half-assed, Garfiel.

66
00:03:04,291 --> 00:03:07,583
It's true Emilia
has failed the trial once.

67
00:03:07,666 --> 00:03:09,416
I can't deny
that she cried her eyes out

68
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:12,583
when it showed her a past
she didn't want to see, either.

69
00:03:12,666 --> 00:03:16,416
But she's still gonna
keep on trying over and over,

70
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,833
unlike you, the guy
who gave up and ran away.

71
00:03:18,916 --> 00:03:20,958
- [Garfiel growls]
- Garfiel...

72
00:03:21,041 --> 00:03:23,333
you have a grudge,
and it's holding you back,

73
00:03:23,416 --> 00:03:25,000
one against your mother,
who deserted you.

74
00:03:25,083 --> 00:03:26,041
[Garfiel gasps]

75
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:29,625
SUBARU: Sorry, man.

76
00:03:29,708 --> 00:03:32,583
While it may be kinder
to beat around the bush,

77
00:03:32,666 --> 00:03:33,333
it's the Natsuki family way

78
00:03:33,416 --> 00:03:35,625
to be blunt
and tell it like it is.

79
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:37,375
No hard feelings.

80
00:03:37,458 --> 00:03:38,375
Your mother left you.

81
00:03:38,458 --> 00:03:42,416
You and Frederica were
abandoned in the Sanctuary.

82
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:45,291
Then after that,
what did you do?

83
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:46,375
[Garfiel gasping]

84
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:51,666
SUBARU: Frederica left
the Sanctuary, too.

85
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:54,625
She believed that you'd
eventually liberate it,

86
00:03:54,708 --> 00:03:57,500
so she left to make
a place in the outside world

87
00:03:57,583 --> 00:03:59,166
for the people living here.

88
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:02,416
But, you, what have you
been doing on the inside?

89
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:04,291
You want to keep it
all closed off,

90
00:04:04,375 --> 00:04:05,583
because you hate your mother

91
00:04:05,666 --> 00:04:07,041
and the outside world
that made her leave you?

92
00:04:07,125 --> 00:04:10,166
Is that what's
really been going on?

93
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,500
Is it 'cause you
don't want to be hurt here?!

94
00:04:12,583 --> 00:04:14,833
- No. What in the hell
do you think you're...

95
00:04:14,916 --> 00:04:16,875
- I'm not gonna know
until you tell me,

96
00:04:16,958 --> 00:04:19,833
so make me understand,
and say something!

97
00:04:19,916 --> 00:04:22,083
If you despise your mother,
then bust out of this place now,

98
00:04:22,166 --> 00:04:24,750
and get revenge on her
or whatever,

99
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:27,666
but stop taking it out
on every single person here!

100
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:30,333
- [gasps]
- You must hate your family,

101
00:04:30,416 --> 00:04:31,875
'cause if you didn't,
then you'd--

102
00:04:31,958 --> 00:04:33,625
- You're wrong!
- [gasps]

103
00:04:34,875 --> 00:04:36,750
- I wanted...

104
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:37,750
I just...

105
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:39,958
- Go on and tell me the truth!

106
00:04:41,125 --> 00:04:42,500
- [shudders]

107
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:44,541
I just--

108
00:04:44,625 --> 00:04:47,750
just wanted my--

109
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:51,041
I just wanted my mom
to finally be happy.

110
00:04:52,958 --> 00:04:54,791
We were in the way.

111
00:04:54,875 --> 00:04:57,791
My sister and I were in the way
of her happiness, weren't we?!

112
00:04:57,875 --> 00:04:58,541
It only makes sense!

113
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:00,708
[sobs]

114
00:05:00,791 --> 00:05:02,416
We were bringin' her down.

115
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:04,750
She couldn't even stand
to look at us.

116
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:06,625
If you're carryin' around
baggage like that,

117
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:08,708
then what's wrong
with dumpin' it somewhere?!

118
00:05:08,791 --> 00:05:11,041
Mom took a chance.

119
00:05:11,125 --> 00:05:13,750
She left so she could find
some joy in her life,

120
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:15,916
so I'm not holdin'
anything against her.

121
00:05:16,958 --> 00:05:19,666
But I saw it.

122
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,875
I saw it in the graveyard.

123
00:05:21,958 --> 00:05:24,875
Right after Mom left here,

124
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:27,000
there was a landslide.

125
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,500
And she died.

126
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:36,125
Why? It's just not fair.

127
00:05:36,208 --> 00:05:38,750
Didn't she take off so
she
could find somethin'
better?

128
00:05:40,375 --> 00:05:42,291
Wasn't the entire point
of leavin' us behind

129
00:05:42,375 --> 00:05:46,500
so she could be free
to find herself again?

130
00:05:46,583 --> 00:05:48,833
If she abandoned us
just to end up dyin'

131
00:05:48,916 --> 00:05:50,500
before she even had the chance

132
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:52,666
to have what she
was lookin' for out there...

133
00:05:53,625 --> 00:05:56,875
then just what in the hell
are we supposed to do?

134
00:05:56,958 --> 00:06:01,500
There's nothin' that I wanted
more than for Mom to be happy.

135
00:06:01,583 --> 00:06:03,125
I wanted her to make me believe

136
00:06:03,208 --> 00:06:05,958
that our sadness and loneliness
had a purpose behind it,

137
00:06:06,041 --> 00:06:07,375
that everything we went through

138
00:06:07,458 --> 00:06:09,458
was the price
to help her chase her dream!

139
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:12,708
I wanted that to be the reason.

140
00:06:12,791 --> 00:06:14,541
I wanted her
to make me hate her!

141
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:22,458
There's no way I'm lettin' you
get back to the outside world.

142
00:06:22,541 --> 00:06:24,666
- [gasps]
- Things changin'

143
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:26,791
ain't gonna make everyone happy.

144
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:29,541
For a lot of us,
nothin's ever gonna get better.

145
00:06:31,916 --> 00:06:34,583
I'm gonna protect them.
You hear me?

146
00:06:34,666 --> 00:06:39,500
I'm gonna defend everyone
and everything within my reach.

147
00:06:39,583 --> 00:06:42,625
I'll use all the power I have
to become a barrier,

148
00:06:42,708 --> 00:06:44,000
a real barrier,

149
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:46,833
one that can separate
the inside from the outside!

150
00:06:46,916 --> 00:06:47,666
- Garfiel, don't!

151
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:52,041
- The Sanctuary,
the people, the old hag,

152
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:53,833
I'll guard 'em all!

153
00:06:53,916 --> 00:06:56,000
No one can do it but me!

154
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:57,875
No one will know but me,

155
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,416
and no one else needs to!

156
00:07:02,916 --> 00:07:05,166
[chorus vocalizing]

157
00:07:05,250 --> 00:07:07,208
[growls]

158
00:07:07,291 --> 00:07:10,666
[roars]

159
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:13,000
- [groans]

160
00:07:13,083 --> 00:07:14,083
EMILIA: Subaru.

161
00:07:15,625 --> 00:07:17,291
- It's okay, Emilia. Thanks.

162
00:07:18,875 --> 00:07:20,625
[grunts]

163
00:07:20,708 --> 00:07:22,958
You're so damn stubborn.

164
00:07:23,041 --> 00:07:26,000
I guess I'll just have to
force you into total submission

165
00:07:26,083 --> 00:07:29,833
to make you realize that you're
just a big, sweet idiot!

166
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:31,291
- [roars]

167
00:07:31,375 --> 00:07:36,083
- You'd better
survive this, body!

168
00:07:36,166 --> 00:07:38,083
<i>Shamac!</i>

169
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:39,833
[heart beating]

170
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,166
Thanks for being there.

171
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,166
- [grunts]

172
00:07:56,666 --> 00:07:59,041
- Come down to my level,
Garfiel!

173
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:01,666
[chorus vocalizing]

174
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:13,083
- [gasps]

175
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:16,541
[gasps]

176
00:08:16,625 --> 00:08:16,666
[vocalizing ends]

177
00:08:19,208 --> 00:08:21,208
[gasping]

178
00:08:22,875 --> 00:08:25,750
Wh-What the hell jus--

179
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:26,958
[groans]

180
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:30,916
[gasps]

181
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,958
Is this my sister's?

182
00:08:34,041 --> 00:08:35,875
But it doesn't make
any damn sense.

183
00:08:35,958 --> 00:08:37,375
- Oh, I don't know.

184
00:08:37,458 --> 00:08:39,916
I mean, who's to say
that there isn't

185
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,750
a really hungry cat
hangin' out inside of it?

186
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:44,958
PUCK:<i> That's all the help</i>
<i>I can give you.</i>

187
00:08:45,041 --> 00:08:47,166
- Apparently,
even when you can't talk,

188
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:50,125
you can still find a way
to annoy me by glowing.

189
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:53,375
All right, look at me.

190
00:08:54,916 --> 00:08:55,375
- Huh?

191
00:08:55,458 --> 00:08:57,083
- If you wanna stop me,

192
00:08:57,166 --> 00:08:58,708
do it with your own hands.

193
00:08:58,791 --> 00:09:00,250
Don't wuss out
and hide behind your blood,

194
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:04,000
you sniveling,
pathetic coward.

195
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:07,250
When are you gonna stop
treating me like a fool?

196
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:09,166
We're going
to the outside world,

197
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:11,125
Emilia's taking on the trial,

198
00:09:11,208 --> 00:09:13,000
and the Sanctuary
will be liberated,

199
00:09:13,083 --> 00:09:15,125
whether you like it or not.

200
00:09:16,708 --> 00:09:17,250
- You don't have any right.

201
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:20,250
Who said you could do that?!

202
00:09:20,333 --> 00:09:22,916
This place
doesn't need to change!

203
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,916
- You know it's not
gonna stay like this forever!

204
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,250
In the same way
we've all been cornered,

205
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:28,416
there's gonna come a time

206
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:31,625
when you'll be
completely helpless on your own,

207
00:09:31,708 --> 00:09:34,083
maybe tomorrow
or maybe even right now.

208
00:09:34,166 --> 00:09:36,958
Learn to accept that, Garfiel.

209
00:09:37,041 --> 00:09:39,166
Then discover what
"strength in numbers" means.

210
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:41,000
- So that's the point
you've been tryin' to make?

211
00:09:41,083 --> 00:09:43,875
What a waste of time!

212
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,833
[blow echoes]

213
00:09:46,916 --> 00:09:47,833
[gasps]

214
00:09:47,916 --> 00:09:50,625
- [gasping]

215
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,375
[chuckles]

216
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:00,833
- [gasps]

217
00:10:02,083 --> 00:10:04,000
- [coughs]
- [tooth clatters]

218
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:06,000
Take a good look.

219
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:08,708
The wall you've been
so desperately afraid of

220
00:10:08,791 --> 00:10:09,125
doesn't even exist.

221
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:12,166
- It does exist,

222
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:13,166
'cause I<i> am</i> the wall!

223
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:16,208
Understand? I stopped here,

224
00:10:16,291 --> 00:10:18,291
and so did the old hag
and everyone else.

225
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:20,000
And that's the end of it,

226
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:21,333
which means it's over!

227
00:10:21,416 --> 00:10:23,291
- Don't just give up
on yourself!

228
00:10:23,375 --> 00:10:24,250
Whenever that voice
inside your head

229
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:27,041
says, "I wanna do it!
I wanna change,"

230
00:10:27,125 --> 00:10:28,208
that's the beginning!

231
00:10:28,291 --> 00:10:30,125
That's where
your starting line is!

232
00:10:30,208 --> 00:10:33,250
When you decide to lift
your head and walk again,

233
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:35,958
no one has the power
to stop you for any reason!

234
00:10:36,041 --> 00:10:37,125
["Realize" playing]

235
00:10:37,208 --> 00:10:40,083
Isn't that right, Garfiel?!

236
00:10:40,166 --> 00:10:43,958
Isn't that right, Emilia?!

237
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:45,958
And...

238
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:50,750
isn't that right, Rem?!

239
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,875
- [growls]

240
00:10:52,958 --> 00:10:55,833
Damn you!

241
00:10:55,916 --> 00:10:57,875
- [gasps]
- [yells]

242
00:10:57,958 --> 00:10:59,833
[heart beating]

243
00:11:06,375 --> 00:11:07,833
- [gasps]

244
00:11:07,916 --> 00:11:09,958
[heartbeat grows louder]

245
00:11:11,916 --> 00:11:14,083
[sputters]

246
00:11:14,166 --> 00:11:15,916
[yells]

247
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,291
- [gasps]

248
00:11:22,458 --> 00:11:23,541
[groans]

249
00:11:34,083 --> 00:11:35,125
- [gasps]

250
00:11:35,208 --> 00:11:37,375
Man, talk about
a bad first impression

251
00:11:37,458 --> 00:11:39,708
for a new technique. [gags]

252
00:11:42,916 --> 00:11:45,083
Aw, come on.
You've gotta be kidding me.

253
00:11:45,166 --> 00:11:47,416
You're really standing?

254
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:50,125
- How tough are you?
- [panting]

255
00:11:50,208 --> 00:11:52,375
I still got some fight left.

256
00:11:52,458 --> 00:11:55,333
Don't underestimate me.

257
00:11:55,416 --> 00:11:57,958
As long as I don't break,

258
00:11:58,041 --> 00:12:00,291
I can...

259
00:12:00,375 --> 00:12:01,250
